The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 November is 93,560 (10,783.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 October, there were 4,569 new confirmed cases (526.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 October, there were 4,234 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 8% (335 extra cases).
